  <title translate="true">Specifying a Uniform Initial Grid</title>
  <body>
    <header>
      <para styleclass="Heading2_atoc_"><text styleclass="Heading1" translate="true">Specifying a Uniform Initial Grid</text></para>
    </header>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">When the user chooses to create a new model, the </text><link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="Initial_Grid_Dialog_Box" styleclass="Normal" translate="true">Initial Grid dialog box</link><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> gives the user the opportunity to specify a grid with uniformly spaced columns and rows. &#160;With PHAST, the layers will also be uniformly spaced. &#160;With MODFLOW, the layers will be horizontal but the layer thicknesses will be specified by the user. </text><conditional-text type="IF" value="FOOTPRINT"/><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">With </text><link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="Footprint_Properties_Dialog_Bo" styleclass="Normal" translate="true">Well Footprints</link><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">, the grid only contains rows and columns.</text><conditional-text type="END"/></para>
  </body>
